race.description: The Timber Pole Haulage Super Maiden Handicap
race.comment: SOUTHAMPTON FLARE (4) was crunched from $1.85 into $1.50 when resuming last start over 1015m at Ballina but after leading for home was run down near the line. Gets a little weight relief under today's scale, strips fitter, and the blinkers go on so he looks a terrific chance to open the account. DANCE GAVIN DANCE (3) debuted last start at Ballina where he stalked SOUTHAMPTON FLARE into the straight and stuck with him all the way, finishing third but just 0.4 lengths behind today's key rival. Plenty of upside and should be thereabouts again. PARFUMIER (12) returns from a spell for new trainer Darren Treacy. Form early last prep at the provincials was strong, albeit on wet tracks. Should come back in good order. KAYAKO (9) is a Spirit Of Boom first starter. Has trialled six times dating back to March, the latest effort the pick. Certainly ready for this. CZECH HER OUT (10) didn't finish too far away first-up at Gosford and can improve enough to play a role in the finish.
